value.value: A condition of mild to moderate high blood pressure that has no identifiable cause.
A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the translocation of the short arm (p36) of chromosome 1 and the long arm (q23-25) of chromosome 3. It is associated with WWTR1/CAMTA1 fusions.
A chromosomal deletion involving the p36 band of chromosome 1. This deletion is associated with 1p36 deletion syndrome.
High blood pressure caused by an underlying medical condition.
A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to loss of all or part of chromosome 4.
A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the loss of all or part of the short arm of chromosome 18 (18p).
Mild to moderate high blood pressure that is caused by an underlying medical condition.
A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the loss of all or part of the long arm of chromosome 6 (6q).
A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to loss of all or part of chromosome 9.
A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to loss of all or part of chromosome 10.
A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to loss of all or part of chromosome 3.
Recurrent nasal polyps with subsequent destruction of the nasal pyramid.
A genetic finding indicating that there is increased activation of the NFkappaB pathway.
A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the loss of all or part of the short arm of chromosome 16 (16p).
A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to loss of all or part of chromosome 1.
A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to loss of all or part of chromosome 18.

A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to the loss of all or part of the sex-determining chromosome Y. It is associated with the development of the accelerated and blast phases of chronic myelogenous leukemia, BCR-ABL1 positive, and various types of carcinomas.

A porphyrin derivative conjugated with a magnesium ion that is found in plant chloroplasts, algae and cyanobacteria. Chlorophyll is essential to the process of photosynthesis. It absorbs light in the blue and red parts of the visible spectrum and transfers the absorbed photon energy to an electron, which is used to produce ATP.
Breast fibrocystic change characterized by the prominence of fibrotic changes in the parenchyma.
